&lt;p&gt;Forum One is a digital agency that helps federal agencies and mission-driven organizations solve complex challenges through strategy, design, technology, and data programs. We are seeking an experienced Senior Project Manager with a strong background managing federal government technology and digital services projects. The ideal candidate has experience working within federal contracting environments, managing multidisciplinary teams, and delivering successful outcomes for government clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead complex federal technology and digital services projects from discovery through deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage scope, schedule, budget, risks, and resources to ensure successful project outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate Agile delivery processes, including sprint planning, backlog refinement, and retrospectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with technical leads to translate requirements into actionable project plans and user stories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify risks and develop mitigation strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial &amp;amp; Operational Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage project budgets, burn rates, forecasts, and resource allocations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track scope changes and support change order processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate project reporting, revenue forecasting, and invoicing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive project profitability and operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Partnership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted advisor and primary point of contact on the project for federal clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate status meetings, project reviews, and stakeholder communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support high client satisfaction and CPARS performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional teams including designers, developers, strategists, and subcontractors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct project health checks and retrospectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support a collaborative, accountable, and high-performing team culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree and 8+ years of project management experience (or Master&#39;s degree and 7+ years), including leading federal government technology, digital services, web, CMS, cloud, data, or digital transformation projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PMP certification required, with strong knowledge of Agile and Scrum methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience managing project budgets, forecasts, staffing plans, resource allocation, and overall project financial performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of federal contracting environments, including Firm Fixed Price (FFP) contracts, FAR/DFARS requirements, and federal procurement processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, presentation, client relationship, and stakeholder management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to obtain and maintain a Public Trust clearance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Forum One?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join a collaborative team that helps government agencies deliver meaningful outcomes through innovative digital solutions. You&#39;ll work alongside talented professionals in a remote-first environment focused on impact, growth, and continuous improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Forum One is an Equal Opportunity Employer.&lt;/p&gt;
